sentence: I wanted this to work too .
I enjoyed reading the books and was eager to play this game well before it came out .
Unfortunately , it is nothing but a start - up and crash - fest .
Perhaps one day they will patch it and on that day I ' ll edit this review .
Until then , google Hogwart ' s Legacy game crashes before you pay for this .

This is the only pop - culture focused game I ' ve looked forward to in years . . . now it will remain as such . . . I ' ll remain hopeful that one day , they will patch this , but before that , I ' m seeking a refund as I ' m posting this .
I ' ll try again later after a few patches .
top line computer , game stops playing after closing the welcome letter !
I was so excited to play this when I bought this yesterday but all I got is wasted hour of trying to open the game as it keeps crashing on me on the Shader thingy .
I was so disappointed cause I really wanna play .
Didn ' t even get past epilepsy warning
In order to change the graphic settings it wants me to confirm with a weird symbol that doesn ' t exist on any keyboard .
Can ' t use the mouse for the dialog box either .
Every game I have is played at high settings on 4K .
But hogwarts set everything to the lowest and won ' t let me change anything .
Crashes continuoulsy and can ' t get passed loading screen
game wont load past warning screan , i ' ve tried everything , making sure computer is updated , varified files , restarted computer many a time , uninstalled and reinstalled .
Trying to reinstall it again right now ( yay more hours cry ) please help ideas welcomed and wanted
I refunded the game after 60 minutes as my system was struggling with framerate and stuttering in cutscenes .
I ' m currently running a Ryzen 5600x , 16gb Vengeance , and 1080Ti , to see how it performs .
Lowest graphic settings and it was stuttering in many of the cutscenes .
Wouldn ' t recommend if you ' re running anything below , say , a 2060 .
Maybe even up to a 3060 . disappointing as I meet the minimum requirements and also am at the recommended too ?
I ' m waiting until March to order a 3060 so maybe then I ' ll try again .
I did get a cringe feeling looking at my characters face .
No matter what I try to do to fix it it just won ' t launch .
I ' ve tried all the guides .
They need to patch this asap .
